":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Scott Butler","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"updated":"2012-08-10T00:37:03.867-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10203","id":"10203","name":"Installation Guide"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"The CentOS 5 installation instructions need to be updated to reflect Eucalyptus 3.1's new package set.  This will be used as the basis for the remaining RHEL and CentOS package installation instructions.  What follows is my current understanding.  Feel free to edit it to help it make more sense.\r\n\r\n\"You will also install each secondary component...\" is contingent on one's desire for an HA installation.\r\n\r\n# Configure the Eucalyptus package repository on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component:\r\n{code}\r\nrpm -Uvh http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/eucalyptus/3.1/rhel/5/x86_64/eucalyptus-release-3.1.noarch.rpm\r\n{code}\r\n# Configure the Euca2ools package repository on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component or Euca2ools:\r\n{code}\r\nrpm -Uvh http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/euca2ools/2.1/rhel/5/x86_64/eucalyptus-release-3.1.noarch.rpm\r\n{code}\r\n# Configure the EPEL package repository on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component or Euca2ools:\r\n{code}\r\nrpm -Uvh http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/eucalyptus/3.1/rhel/5/x86_64/epel-release-5.noarch.rpm\r\n{code}\r\n# Configure the ELRepo repository on each host that will run Walrus:\r\n{code}\r\nrpm -Uvh http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/eucalyptus/3.1/rhel/5/x86_64/elrepo-release-5.noarch.rpm\r\n{code}\r\n# If you have a Eucalyptus subscription you will have received a package that grants you access to VMware and SAN components.  If you wish to use either of these components, install this package on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component.  Otherwise, skip this step.\r\n{code}\r\nrpm -Uvh eucalyptus-enterprise-release-3.1-1.noarch.rpm\r\n{code}\r\n# If your planned Walrus host runs a Xen kernel (possible, but not recommended), install the {{kmod-drbd83-xen}} package on that host.  Otherwise, skip this step.\r\n{code}\r\nyum install kmod-drbd83-xen\r\n{code}\r\n# Install the Eucalyptus cloud controller software on each planned CLC host:\r\n{code}\r\nyum groupinstall eucalyptus-cloud-controller\r\n{code}\r\n# Install the Eucalyptus node controller software on each planned NC host.  Clouds that use the VMware hypervisor do not have NCs; if you plan to use VMware then skip this step.\r\n{code}\r\nyum install eucalyptus-nc\r\n{code}\r\n# Install the software for the remaining Eucalyptus components.  The following example shows most components being installed on the same host.  You can use different hosts for each component.\r\n{code}\r\nyum install eucalyptus-cc eucalyptus-sc eucalyptus-walrus\r\n{code}\r\n# If you have a Eucalyptus subscription and plan to use the VMware hypervisor, install the Eucalyptus VMware broker software on each CC host:\r\n{code}\r\nyum install eucalyptus-enterprise-vmware-broker\r\n{code}\r\n# If you have a Eucalyptus subscription and plan to use Eucalyptus's SAN capabilities, install the Eucalyptus SAN adapter software on each SC host:\r\n{code}\r\nyum install eucalyptus-enterprise-storage-san\r\n{code}\r\n# After you have installed Eucalyptus, test multicast connectivity between each CLC and Walrus, SC, and VMware broker host.\r\n## Run the following receiver command on the CLC:\r\n{code}\r\njava -classpath /usr/share/eucalyptus/jgroups-2.11.1.Final.jar org.jgroups.tests.McastReceiverTest -mcast_addr 224.10.10.10 -port 5555\r\n{code}\r\n## Run the following sender command on each Walrus host:\r\n{code}\r\njava -classpath /usr/share/eucalyptus/jgroups-2.11.1.Final.jar org.jgroups.tests.McastSenderTest -mcast_addr 224.10.10.10 -port 5555\r\n{code}\r\n## Repeat the previous step on each SC host and VMware broker host\r\n## If you are installing an HA environment, repeat these tasks with the second CLC.\r\n\r\nYour installation is now complete.","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"Redo CentOS 5 package installation instructions","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=gholms","name":"gholms","key":"gholms","accountId":"557058:6e5fdc25-c797-4d3d-8fd4-55c3c4ed99b0","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%2